  "texts": [
    "Additionally, there were notable rates of chronic conditions, including diabetes (7.9%), hypertension (23.5%), and hyperlipidemia (17.3%).",
    "Lifestyle factors were also recorded, with 18.9% having a smoking history and 15.3% with a history of alcohol consumption.",
    "In terms of emergency severity, 2.8% of cases were classified as critical or severe, while 14.7% were urgent, and the majority, 82.5%, were less urgent.",
    "The diversity of cardiovascular conditions was evident in the primary diagnoses.",
    "(Supplementary Table S2)"
  ]
}